STRENGTH-ROUTER CONTROL GROUPS  (same 20 numbers, truth=correct_label, FAIR=one-shot)
  A  raw single-shot      :  1/20 (  5%)   floor: model does modulo+label in head
  B  decompose, no block  :  5/20 ( 25%)   model computes remainders itself, then labels
  C_fair block-offload    :  1/20 (  5%)   <- CORRECT remainders, model labels ONE-SHOT (no elim)
  D_fair placebo (wrong)  :  1/20 (  5%)   WRONG remainders handed in, one shot
  C_scaffold (inflated)   : 17/20 ( 85%)   blocks + rewind + prune (menu-elimination)
  E_elim_stub (no skill)  :  9/20 ( 45%)   NO-reasoning model under the SAME scaffold
  ATTRIBUTION:
    honest block-offload (C_fair - A) = +0
    remainders load-bearing (C_fair - D_fair) = +0
    elimination crutch (C_scaffold - E_elim_stub) = +8  (if ~0, the inflated arm was the menu, not the model)
